rComments: Class seemed fair enough- three exams & you get to drop your lowest one- however the final (which is 50% of the total grade) was extremely difficult and dropped the grades of not only myself but also everyone else that I knew in the class.  A lot of the questions seemed open to interpretation so I don't know that studying any more would have helped
I retract my statement. NOT an easy class because of the ridiculously tricky, cumulative final! It dropped the grades of everyone I know.

Animal Behavior is a really easy class and Weatherhead is a good instructor. He's very clear and explains things well. The exams are easy as long as you studied. You get to drop your lowest exam which is nice too.

This class is extremely easy to study for, only 3 regular exams and the final exam (you get to drop your lowest regular exam grade), and Weatherhead is an awesome professor. Class is required because he writes everything on the board. Exams are all multiple choice and there a lot of videos that you watch in lecture! TAKE THIS!!
